{"lemma":"عِصابَة","slug":"عِصابَة","root":"ع.ص.ب","root_slug":"ع-ص-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-ص-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":1,"pos_tags":["noun"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n29284"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%90%D8%B5%D8%A7%D8%A8%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"union, league, federation"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"gang (organized crime syndicate)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"bandage, dressing (on a wound)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"headcloth, headband"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"From عَصَبَ (ʕaṣaba, “to bind”)."},"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n29284","headword_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ","root":"ESb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing with which another thing is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round;"},{"kind":"text","text":"as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which the head is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, Mgh, O, TA;) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a thing with which a thing other than the head is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything, such as a piece of rag,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fillet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bandage, with which a broken limb,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a wound, is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"is termed thus, i. e."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbN","text_ar":"عِصَابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a turban;"},{"kind":"text","text":"syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAmapN","text_ar":"عِمَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (A, Mgh, Msb, K, TA:) or this [in the TA by mistake written"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EmAmp","text_ar":"عمامة"},{"kind":"text","text":"] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a small thing that serves as a covering for the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"such as a kerchief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a fillet,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"being wound round it;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and what is larger is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EimaAmapN","text_ar":"عِمَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": ('Ináyeh of Esh-Shiháb, MF, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whatever is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound, round the head,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether it be"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a turban"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a kerchief"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a piece of rag:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, from an explanation of a trad.:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"[likewise] signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a turban,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"anything with which the head is bound,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"wound round:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O:) the pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EiSaAbapN","text_ar":"عِصَابَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSaAy^ibu","text_ar":"عَصَايِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, TA.) El-Farezdak says,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"warakobN kaA^an~a Alr~iyHa taTolubu minohumu\n                      \n                     \n                        lahaA salabFA mino ja*obihaA biAlEaSaAy^ibi"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And a company of riders"},{"kind":"text","text":"in such a state that it seemed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"as though the wind desired to take for itself spoil from them, by its dragging away the turbans"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: he means that the wind untwisted their turbans by its violence, as though it despoiled them thereof. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence] (assumed tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A crown."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSobN","text_ar":"عَصْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter half. ―         -b4-  And see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuSobapN","text_ar":"عُصْبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in four places. ―         -b5-  And for the pl. applied to winds, see 1, former half."}],"source_refs":["K","TA","L","A","Mgh","Msb","S","O"]}]}}